article.description: Michael Karena led Wright State with 17 points and six rebounds in the Raiders' 68-50 victory over Division III Albion on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Wright State defeats Division III Albion 68-50
article.linkText: Wright State defeats Division III Albion 68-50
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio -- Michael Karena led Wright State with 17 points and six rebounds in the Raiders' 68-50 victory over Division III Albion on Tuesday night. Karena was 8 of 12 from the floor as the Raiders (3-4) shot 51.8 percent. Biggie Minnis added 10 points. Wright State won the game in the paint where it outscored Albion 46-18. Travell Oakes scored 13 points for the Britons (3-1) with Jibreel Hussein adding 12. Albion shot just 31.4 percent. Of their 16 field goals, seven came from beyond the arc. Wright State led 34-22 at halftime with the help of a 7-3 run to end the first 20 minutes. The Raiders led by double figures the entire second half. A 10-0 run made it a 24-point margin at 56-32 with 9:08 left, which proved to be the Raiders' largest lead.
